    <div class="container">
      Temple Muay Thai is more than just a gym. It's a family of passionate and
      dedicated Muay Thai practitioners who share a common goal: to spread the
      love for the art of eight limbs to the community of Asheville. Whether you
      are a beginner or a seasoned fighter, you will find a place to learn,
      grow, and have fun at Temple Muay Thai.

      <h3>Our History</h3>

      <p>
        Temple Muay Thai was founded on June 3rd of 2020 by Jesse Reyna, who has
        over eight years of experience in Muay Thai alone, including training,
        fighting, and coaching1. Jesse has trained under numerous highly
        experienced coaches from around the United States1. He started Temple
        Muay Thai in the parks of Asheville, North Carolina, with a few students
        and a lot of enthusiasm. Soon, he attracted more and more people who
        wanted to learn from him and join his vision. In 2021, Temple Muay Thai
        moved to its current location inside Oakley Wrestling Club at River
        Ridge market place1, where it continues to grow and thrive.
      </p>

      <h3>Our Mission</h3>

      <p>
        Our mission is to provide the best possible Muay Thai training in
        Asheville, with a focus on quality, safety, and fun. We want to help our
        students achieve their goals, whether they are fitness, self-defense, or
        competition. We also want to create a positive and supportive
        environment where everyone feels welcome and respected. We believe that
        Muay Thai is not only a sport, but also a way of life that can improve
        your mind, body, and spirit.
      </p>

      <h3>Our Team</h3>

      <p>
        Our team consists of experienced and qualified coaches who are
        passionate about Muay Thai and teaching. They are:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item">
          Jesse Reyna: Owner/Sr. Head Muay Thai Coach. He has 8 years of Muay
          Thai experience, 4 years teaching Muay Thai, and trained under
          multiple notable Muay Thai coaches across the US. He has a traditional
          Muay Thai style1.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          TBA: Jr. Head Muay Thai Coach. He has 5 years of Muay Thai experience,
          3 years teaching Muay Thai, and trained and fought in Thailand. He is
          a 3x amateur champion across multiple promotions. He has a traditional
          Muay Thai style1.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          Dathan (Eden) Maney: Assistant/Kids Muay Thai Coach. He has 2 years of
          Muay Thai experience and recently promoted to coach. He is actively
          fighting for Temple MT and trained under Coach Jesse1.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Our Classes</h3>

      <p>
        We offer classes for all levels and ages, from kids to adults. Our
        classes are:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item">
          Kids Muay Thai: For ages 6-12. A fun and safe way to introduce kids to
          the basics of Muay Thai and martial arts. They will learn discipline,
          respect, confidence, coordination, and self-defense skills.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          Beginners Muay Thai: For ages 13+. A class for those who are new to
          Muay Thai or want to refresh their skills. They will learn the
          fundamentals of Muay Thai, such as stance, footwork, punches, kicks,
          knees, elbows, clinch, and defense.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          Intermediate/Advanced Muay Thai: For ages 13+. A class for those who
          have some experience in Muay Thai or want to challenge themselves.
          They will learn more advanced techniques, combinations, drills,
          sparring, and conditioning.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          Women's Only Muay Thai: For ages 13+. A class for women who want to
          learn Muay Thai in a comfortable and supportive environment. They will
          learn the same curriculum as the other classes but with an emphasis on
          self-defense and empowerment.
        </li>
      </ul>
